 python3,
 python3-gi,
 gir1.2-gstreamer-1.0,
 gstreamer1.0-plugins-bad,
 v4l2loopback-dkms
Recommends: gstreamer1.0-icamerasrc
Description: On-demand camera bridge for Intel IPU7 (Lunar Lake)
 Enables Intel IPU7 cameras on Linux by bridging icamerasrc to a
 v4l2loopback device (/dev/video99) and PipeWire, with on-demand
 HAL activation: the camera hardware initialises only when an
 application opens it, and is fully released when the application stops.
 .
 A single GStreamer process holds a static dual-source pipeline so that
 /dev/video99 is always present for applications to enumerate, while the
 actual camera hardware stays idle until needed.
 .
 Requires icamerasrc and the Intel IPU7 Camera HAL to be installed separately.
